      "notes": [
        {
          "category": "summary",
          "text": "An attacker with access to the IEC 61850 network with knowledge of how to reproduce the attack, as well as the IP addresses of the different IEC 61850 access points (of IEDs/products), can force the device to reboot, which renders the device inoperable for approximately 60 seconds. \u00a0This vulnerability affects only products with IEC 61850 interfaces.CVE-2021-27196 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 7.5 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).",
          "title": "Vulnerability Summary"
        }
